{meta: title Poison Love}
{meta: artist Hank Snow}
{meta: composer Elmer Laird}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]All your poison love has stained the life blood in my heart and soul [G7]dear
[C]And I know my life will never be the same
[G7]All my pleas and prayers have been in vain for you and you alone dear
[C]And you know that you are guilty of the shame
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]Into each life a love is born for one and one alone dear
[C]The love I chose was surely not for me
[G7]All your poison love has stained the life blood in my heart and soul dear
[C]And I know our love was never meant to be
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[G7]But still my heart cries out for you and you alone my darling
[C]And fate will never ever let me go
[G7]All my pleas and prayers have been in vain for you and you alone dear
[C]And my better judgment tells me to say no
{end_of_verse}

